Class AbstractDefault

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
CodeTableCodeDefault, SvrBlobDefault, SvrBooleanDefault, SvrDateDefault, SvrDateTimeDefault, SvrDoubleDefault, SvrFloatDefault, SvrInt16Default, SvrInt32Default, SvrInt64Default, SvrInt8Default, SvrMoneyDefault, SvrStringDefault
public abstract class AbstractDefault
extends AbstractClientDomainPlugIn
implements DomainDefault

An abstract super-class for domain default value plug-ins. Custom default value plug-ins should never try to implement the DomainDefault interface directly; they should extend either this abstract class or an existing default value plug-in implementation.

Method Detail

getName

public java.lang.String getName()
Gets the name of the plug-in. This is usually the simple name used to identify the plug-in when loaded. Many different plug-in classes may share the same name if they implement the same type of behavior. For example, "converter" may be used as the name of a plug-in that performs data conversion operations, but there may be different "converter" classes implementing these operations.

Specified by:
getName in interface PlugIn
Returns:
The name "default".
